<TITLE> Maldives draw with Nepal, India edge out Afghanistan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 05 (bdnews24.com)  Defending champions Maldives drew 1-1 with Nepal in their Group A match of the Sixth SAFF Championship at Bangabandhu National Stadium on Saturday. Maldives took the lead in the 61st minute with a goal from Ahmed Tariq. However, Nepal leveled the match with a goal from Jumanu Rai eight minutes from time. India, three-time SAFF champions and 2008 runners up, beat Afghanistan 1-0 with difficulty in the second match of the day at Bangabandhu Stadium, with a goal from Jeje Lalphekhula in the 83rd minute. "Afghanistan played well and came close to scoring twice and we were lucky to snatch the full three points," Indian coach Sukhwinder Singh said at the post-match briefing. Hosts Bangladesh, after a 4-1 win against Bhutan on Friday, will be looking to seal their semifinal spot with a win against Pakistan in a critical Group B match on Sunday. b
